Preconditions:
- The input `accounts` is a 2D integer array.
- The dimensions of `accounts` are `m x n`, where `m` represents the number of customers and `n` represents the number of banks.
- Each element `accounts[i][j]` in the `accounts` array represents the amount of money the `i`th customer has in the `j`th bank.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the wealth of the richest customer.
- The wealth of a customer is calculated by summing up the amounts of money they have in all banks.
- The richest customer is the one with the highest wealth among all customers.